Actually, I don't choose to see only the negative side, I simply recognize that it is there.  I also recognize that there is a positive side as well.  A glass that is half-full is also half-empty.   And as I pointed out a while back, the really interesting question is if you drink all the remaining water in the glass, is it then full or empty?  Both, of course.<br>
<br>
This is true for the POTC quest.  For those of us who do tradeskills or love puzzle-quests, it is a fun way to introduce a new spell.  And for those of us who focus solely on raiding and XPing with no thought for tradeskilling, the material rewards, in terms of what is available in the game, are not really worth the time and expense (the person who completed the quest first estimated his expenses at 15K).  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>I just ignore Scirroco on his opinons of Verant because he is always trying to make it into some kind of confrontation that has never existed.</b><br>
